 semimajor axes larger than 200 AU and no other bodies with similar perihelion distances but smaller
 semimajor axes have yet been discovered. We favor mechanism 4, since it produces an orbital element
 distribution that is more consistent with the observations, unless 2000 CR 105 and 2003 VB 12
